    <description><![CDATA[<div class="featured-image">
                <img src="/img/blobbridge.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">
            </div><figure><a class="lightgallery" href="/games/blob-bridge/images/feature_graphic.png" title="" data-thumbnail="/games/blob-bridge/images/feature_graphic.png" data-sub-html="<h2>A Hyper Casual Color-Matching Game You’ll Love!</h2>"><img  loading="lazy" src=https://rustycruiselabs.github.io/games/blob-bridge/images/feature_graphic.png    height="500" width="1024"></a><figcaption class="image-caption">A Hyper Casual Color-Matching Game You’ll Love!</figcaption>
    </figure>
<h2 id="overview" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#overview" class="header-mark"></a>Overview</h2><p>Blob Bridge was my submission for the <strong>Gamedev.js Game Jam 2025</strong>. It started as a small, relaxed project—a break from more intense development work. Out of 416 entries, the game ranked <strong>158th</strong>, earning a <strong>3.4/5</strong> rating for gameplay, which I&rsquo;m quite happy with, especially since gameplay was always my main priority.</p>
<p>That said, due to time constraints, the gameplay wasn’t fully realized during the jam. After 2 months of iterative development, the <strong>full mobile version</strong> of Blob Bridge is now available on the <strong>Google Play Store</strong> and <strong>Apple App Store</strong>, bringing the original concept to life!</p>]]></description>
